adjectives.description: prograde (comparative more prograde, superlative most prograde)

entries.meaning: (astronomy) Moving in a forward direction, especially with respect to other bodies in the same system.
(geology) Being a metamorphic change resulting from a higher pressure or temperature.

verbs.description: prograde (third-person singular simple present progrades, present participle prograding, simple past and past participle prograded)

entries.meaning: (geology) Of sediment, to build out seawards in conditions of marine regression.
